'''Ahmed Ihab Ahmed''', known as '''Ahmed Qasem''' ({{langx|ar|أحمد قاسم|[[Ahmad|ʾAḥmad]] [[Qasim (name)|Qāsim]]}} pronounced {{IPA|ar|ˈ(ʔ)aħmad ˈqaː.sɪm|}}; born 12 July 2003), is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Nashville SC]]. Born in Sweden, he plays for the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]].

[[File:Ahmed Qasem Revolution Nashville 6.25.25-196.jpg|thumb|Qasem with [[Nashville SC]] in 2025]]

== International career ==
Born in Sweden, Qasem is of [[Palestinian]] and [[Swedish Iraqis|Iraqi]] descent.<ref>[https://x.com/FutbolPalestine/status/1791092075053621442]</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://watananews.com/516942/|title=هل سيمثل أحمد قاسم المنتخب العراقي|date=9 March 2026|website=وطنا نيوز}}</ref> He has represented Sweden internationally at [[Sweden men's national under-17 football team|under-17]], [[Sweden national under-18 football team|under-18]], [[Sweden men's national under-19 football team|under-19]] and [[Sweden national under-21 football team|under-21]] levels.<ref>{{SvFF player|id=a6347645-039b-4cad-a77b-503f1a3d04d0}}</ref>
On 11 May 2026, Qasem's request to switch allegiance to Iraq was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref name="FIFA-Change"/> He was called up to the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]] for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |title=غراهام ارنولد يعلن لكم القائمة النهائية للمنتخب الوطني العراقي لخوض المعسكر التدريبي في إسبانيا قبل المغادرة إلى نهائيات كأس العالم |url=https://x.com/IraqNT_EN/status/2056771613392003532 |website=X|publisher=Iraq National Team|date=19 May 2026 |format=Tweet}}</ref>

On 29 May 2026, Qasem made his senior international debut for Iraq in their pre-World Cup friendly against [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]], starting the match and playing 65 minutes before being replaced by [[Jussef Nasrawe]] as Iraq continued their preparations for the upcoming [[2026 FIFA World Cup|FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ahmed Qasem: World Cup profile - Nashville SC & Iraq forward|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/ahmed-qasem-world-cup-profile-nashville-sc-iraq-forward|work=mlssoccer.com|date=3 June 2026 |accessdate=6 June 2026|lang=en|archive-date=6 June 2026|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20260606090557/https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/ahmed-qasem-world-cup-profile-nashville-sc-iraq-forward|url-status=live}}</ref>

